cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CL 

This paper involves the use of deep learning for image search, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of metadata and annotations for search, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of large datasets and the need for efficient search also suggests multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential use of this tool in pathology education, which could involve natural language processing (cs.CL) for text-based search and retrieval.
